
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-smith-ipv6-link-locals-apps-00.txt'>
    <title>"How to use IPv6 Link-Local Addresses in Applications", Mark Smith</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-smith-ipv6-link-locals-apps-00.txt</link>
    <description>IPv6 Link-Local addresses can be used by applications.  Doing so when possible will provide robustness and security benefits to the application.  This memo describes the properties of Link-Local addresses and the benefits and limitations of using them in applications.  It then describes how to use them in applications that use the Sockets API.</description>
    <dc:date>2015-10-19T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
